Chichikov pressed is face against the window of the light spring britzka. No souls? Where were the little, smashed roofs of the peasantry? The estates were clear! And yet, who had made those furrows in that field? Who had gathered the hay into the barn over there? This was the distinguishing mark of Rus, setting it apart from other nations. In Rus they had achieved what the Englishman could only dream of: a yeomanry that existed and didn’t exist….
